Public safety is the primary concern of the Town of Annetta. Both domestic and wild animals can present a public health or safety hazard. If you feel you are in danger or have been injured by a dom estic or wild animal, call 911 or if it is a potential safety concern, contact the Parker County Sheriff's Department at (817) 594-8845. If there is a non-emergency issue, please call (817) 441-5770 or email info@annettatx.gov . The Town's Animal Control Ordinance is Ordinance 158.
